<hw>lap-straked</hw> }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Made with boards whose edges lap one over another;
clinker-built; -- said of boats. Contrasted with
<contr>carvel-built</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lap-jointed, overlapping.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lap up</ent>⟦br⟧
